Name: readiness_assessment
Description:
completion of the application
rationalization readiness assessment

Name: identify_requirements
Description: identification of applications performing core mission services and applications providing support or other supplementary functions
Notes: 0 indicates that agency has developed a Requirements Landscape

Name: questionnaire
Description: creation of agency-specific list of questions that captures all relevant financial, business, and technical information and reporting requirements for each application
Notes: Questionnaire provides the foundation for Application Rationalization

Name: questionnaires_sent
Description: number of in-scope program offices that received the same questionnaire

Name: CPIC_report
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and CPIC report(s)
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: financial_reporting_tools
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via financial reporting tools
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: authorization_to_operate_lists_and_management_tools
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via authorization to operate lists and management tools
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: cybersecurity_assessment_and_management_tools
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via cybersecurity assessment and management tools
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: SLO_tools_and_inventories
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via SLO tools
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: CMDB_tools
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via CDDB tools
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: CDM_tools
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via CDM tools
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: COOP_and_DR_plans
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via COOP and DR plans
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: DCIM_tools
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via DCIM
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: data_management_systems
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via data management systems
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: hardware_tracking_systems
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via hardware tracking systems
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: licenses_SLAs
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via licenses and SLAs
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: security_operations_tools
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via security operations tools
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: SAM_tools
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via security and operations tools
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: virtualization_management_system
Description: determination of inventory discrepancy between questionnaire responses and inventory as ascertained via virtualization management systems
Notes: 0 indicates a disparity between questionnaire responses and information from existing inventory sources

Name: application_onboarding
Description: creation of a new application onboarding process, wherein the relevant information captured in the questionnaire is reported for all new applications purchased from vendors or developed by or for the agency
Notes: 0 confirms creation of application onboarding process

Name: effectiveness
Description: the degree to which an application is a solution for the goal agencies are trying to achieve (Likert scale)
Values:
very low effectiveness
low effectiveness
moderate effectiveness
high effectiveness
very high effectiveness

Name: mission_criticality
Description: the degree to which an application is critical in supporting and executing the agencies’ mission (Likert scale)
Values:
very low mission criticality
low mission criticality
moderate mission criticality
high mission criticality
very high mission criticality

Name: utilization
Description: the degree to which an application is used (Likert scale)
Values:
very low usage
low usage
moderate usage
strong usage
high usage

Name: complexity
Description:
the degree of customization, unique features, and functions enabled by an
application (Likert scale)
Values:
very low complexity
low complexity
moderate complexity
high complexity
very high complexity

Name: usability
Description: the degree of ease for the user to operate or learn how to use an application (Likert scale)
Values:
very low usability
low usability
moderate usability
high usability
very high usability

Name: technical_requirements_bandwidth
Description: the level of bandwidth required for an application to run, in megabits per second (mbps)
Notes: rounded to nearest whole number

Name: technical_requirements_data
Description: the level of data required for an application to run, in petabytes (PB)
Notes: in petabytes

Name: version_control
Description: number of official application updates within a given year
Notes: rounded to whole number

Name: dependencies_upstream_exist
Description: determination of the presence of code, databases, and functionality on which the application depends

Name: dependencies_downstream_exist
Description: determination of the presence of the code, databases, and functionality that depend on the application

Name: scalability_adaptability
Description: the degree to which an application can be scaled to onboard new users and can it be augmented to fit the needs of new user groups (Likert scale)
Values:
very low scalability/adaptability
low scalability/adaptability
moderate scalability/adaptability
high scalability/adaptability
very high scalability/adaptability

Name: security_standards
Description: the degree to which an application is protected against security attacks and conforms to agency risk tolerance models (Likert scale)
Values:
very low security standards
low security standards
moderate security standards
high security standards
very high security standards

Name: NIST_ID.AM
Description: use of asset management in alignment with agency mission and risk strategy

Name: NIST_ID.BE
Description: use of agency environment (mission, objectives, stakeholders, and activities) to inform cybersecurity strategy

Name: NIST_ID.GV
Description: use of agency governance (policies, procedures, and processes) to inform compliance with legal and regulatory requirements, and management of cybersecurity risk

Name: NIST_ID.RA
Description: determination that agency understands cybersecurity risk to its operations, assets, and workforce

Name: NIST_ID.RM
Description: determination that operational risk decisions are based on agency priorities, constraints, risk tolerance, and assumptions

Name: NIST_ID.SC
Description: determination that supply chain risk management is based on agency priorities, constraints, risk tolerance, and assumptions

Name: NIST_PR.AC
Description: determination that only authorized users, processes, and devices can access physical and logical assets and facilities; and that management of physical and logical assets and facilities is aligned with assessed security and privacy risks

Name: NIST_PR.AT
Description: determination that agency workforce are provided cybersecurity awareness and education in alignment with their specific roles and responsibilities, and with agency policies, procedures, and agreements

Name: NIST_PR.DS
Description: determination that data are managed in alignment with assessed security and privacy risks

Name: NIST_PR.IP
Description: determination that security policies, processes, and procedures are in place and implemented to protect information systems and assets

Name: NIST_PR.MA
Description: determination that maintenance of IT infrastructure occurs according to  policies and procedures

Name: NIST_PR.PT
Description: determination that management of security solutions aligns with related policies, procedures, and agreements

Name: NIST_DE.AE
Description: determination that anomalous activity is detected and assessed for potential impact

Name: NIST_DE.CM
Description: determination that information systems and assets are continuously monitored to detect cybersecurity events, and to verify the effectiveness of protective measures

Name: NIST_DE.DP
Description: determination that detection processes and procedures are maintained and tested to ensure awareness of anomalous activity

Name: NIST_RS.RP
Description: determination that response plans are maintained and executed during and/or after cybersecurity incidents

Name: NIST_RS.CO
Description: determination that responses to cybersecurity incidents are coordinated between internal and external stakeholders in accordance with response plans

Name: NIST_RS.AN
Description: determination that analysis is performed to inform an effective response to cybersecurity incidents, and to support disaster recovery

Name: NIST_RS.MI
Description: determination that activities are performed to contain, mitigtate, and resolve cybersecurity incidents

Name: NIST_RS.IM
Description: determination that the agency seeks to improve cybersecurity responses incorporates lessons learned from cybersecurity incidents into response plans and strategies

Name: NIST_RC.RP
Description: determination that recovery plans are maintained and executed during and/or after cybersecurity incidents

Name: NIST_RC.IM
Description: determination that the agency seeks to improve cybersecurity responses incorporates lessons learned from cybersecurity incidents into recovery plans and strategies

Name: NIST_RC.CO
Description: determination that recovery activities in response to cybersecurity incidents are coordinated between internal and external stakeholders in accordance with response plans

Name: RTO
Description: determination of recovery time objective (RTO)

Name: RTO_cost
Description: determination of cost associated with recovery time objective (RTO)

Name: RPO
Description: determination of recovery point objective (RTO)

Name: RPO_cost
Description: determination of cost associated with recovery point objective (RTO)

Name: RTA
Description: determination of recovery point objective (RTA)

Name: RTA_cost
Description: determination of cost associated with recovery point objective (RTA)

Name: dependencies_upstream_identity
Description: determination of the code, databases, and functionality on which the application depends

Name: dependencies_downstream_identity
Description: determination of the code, databases, and functionality that depend on the application

Name: duplication
Description: review of the application inventory for duplication

Name: TCO
Description: the sum of current-state direct and indirect costs associated with owning and operating an application over a given year (USD)

Name: OpEx_internal_labor

Name: OpEx_external_labor

Name: OpEx_outside_services_consulting

Name: OpEx_outside_services_managed_service_providers

Name: OpEx_outside_services_cloud_service_providers

Name: OpEx_software

Name: OpEx_software_expense

Name: OpEx_software_maintenance_support

Name: OpEx_software_depreciation

Name: OpEx_hardware

Name: OpEx_hardware_expense

Name: OpEx_hardware_lease

Name: OpEx_hardware_maintenance_support
Description: annual operating expenditures associated with hardware maintenance and support (USD)

Name: OpEx_hardware_depreciation

Name: OpEx_facilities_and_power

Name: OpEx_facilities_and_power_lease
Description: annual operating expenditures associated with data center leases (USD)

Name: OpEx_facilities_and_power_maintenance_and_support

Name: OpEx_telecom

Description: annual operating expenditures associated with telecom maintenance and support (USD)

Name: OpEx_telecom_depreciation
Description:
annual depreciation of capitalized telecom
expenditures (USD)

Name: OpEx_other
Description: annual miscellaneous operating expenditures (USD)

Name: OpEx_internal_services
Description: annual charges from other intragovernmental groups that provide shared services (USD)

Name: CapEx_internal_labor

Name: CapEx_external_labor
Description: annual expenditures for external labor above the capitalization threshold (USD)

Name: CapEx_hardware

Name: CapEx_telecom

Name: IT_Tower_delivery_operations_center

Name: IT_Tower_security_compliance_dr

Name: IT_Tower_IT_management_IT_management_strategic_planning

Name: certifications
Description: annual expenditures related to employee certifications (USD)

Name: reassignments
Description: annual expenditures related to employee reassignments (USD)

Name: HR
Description: annual HR-related expenditures associated with onboarding new employees and leveraging HR offices for change management processes (USD)

Name: IT_training
Description: annual expenditures associated with training of current employees and hiring of new employees (USD)

Name: software_patching
Description: annual expenditures associated with manual software patching (USD)

Name: ATO
Description: annual expenditures associated with attaining ATO(s) (USD)

Name: outlier
Description: presence of cost outlier(s) in the application inventory
Notes: 0 confirms presence in the agency's IT portfolio

Name: scoring_methodology
Description: scoring methodology used to implement an application rationalization strategy
Example: Gartner’s Tolerate, Invest, Migrate, Eliminate (TIME) methodology
Notes: Agency-determined methodology

Name: application_score
Description: application score on agency-defined ranking or merit scale
Notes: In agency-determined format

Name: communications_strategy
Description: creation of a communications strategy that enables stakeholders to learn about the scoring process, understand how information will be shared, and provide feedback

Name: review
Description: presence of applications with low business value and high technical fit
Notes: 0 confirms presence in the agency's IT portfolio

Name: reward
Description: presence of applications with high business value and high technical fit
Notes: 0 confirms presence in the agency's IT portfolio

Name: refresh
Description: presence of applications with high business value and low technical fit
Notes: 0 confirms presence in the agency's IT portfolio

Name: remove
Description: presence of applications with low business value and low technical fit
Notes: 0 confirms presence in the agency's IT portfolio

Name: hosting_options
Description:
determination of hosting options based on future-state TCO, improved service
delivery, and customer satisfaction

Name: assessing_current-state_cost
Description: annual up-front costs associated with assessing the current-state (USD)

Name: planning_migration_costs
Description: annual up-front costs associated with migration planning (USD)

Name: stakeholder_costs
Description: annual up-front costs associated with attaining stakeholder buy-in (USD)

Name: parallel_systems_costs
Description: annual up-front costs associated with running parallel systems (USD)

Name: vendor_management_costs
Description: annual up-front costs associated with vendor management (USD)

Name: training_reskilling_costs
Description: annual up-front costs associated with training and reskilling (USD)

Name: refactoring_replatforming_cost
Description: annual up-front costs associated with refactoring and replatforming existing applications (USD)

Name: migration_strategy
Description: creation of an IT migration strategy that includes a communications strategy, a vendor management plan, a workforce development plan, and a migration timeline, and that attains buy-in from key stakeholders
